              <title>JIME issues Open Educational Resources Special Edition</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/4915</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/4915</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>The Journal of Interactive Media in  Education has published a special edition on Open Educational Resources today.&nbsp;  The journal, which recently moved from its old website to an Open Journal  Systems website, has been published online by The Open University since it was  founded in 1996.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The OER special edition consists of  an introduction and five papers selected from those which were presented at the  OER10 conference at the University of Cambridge in March 2010.&nbsp; The papers  address a number of significant challenges in the design, use and embedding of  OERs.&nbsp; The introduction is by Tom  Boyle, of London Metropolitan University.</p>
<p>Andy  Lane&rsquo;s paper is called &ldquo;Designing for innovation around  OER&rdquo; in which he discusses the different design approaches for OERs compared to  those used for &lsquo;closed&rsquo; educational resources.&nbsp; Tom  Browne and colleagues paper is a reflective case study called  &ldquo;The challenges of OER to Academic practice&rdquo;.&nbsp; Windle and colleagues raise a  number of issues for successful OER deployment and reuse in &ldquo;Sharing and reuse  in OER: experiences gained from open reusable learning objects in health&rdquo;.&nbsp;  Greaves et al report impressive results improving pass rates in &ldquo;Repurposing  with a purpose: A story with a happy ending&rdquo;.&nbsp; The final paper in the special  issue is by Qi and Boyle which explores &ldquo;Dimensions of culturally sensitive  factors in the design and development of learning  objects&rdquo;.</p>
<p>&nbsp;You can find the Special Edition at  <a title="http://jime.open.ac.uk/jime/issue/view/2010-OER" href="http://jime.open.ac.uk/jime/issue/view/2010-OER">http://jime.open.ac.uk/jime/issue/view/2010-OER</a></p>]]></description>
