                    <item>
              <title>Activity: 30 mins: Introduction to OERs</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/2530</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/2530</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<ul>
</ul>
<p><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_educational_resources" target="_self"><strong>What are OERs (Open Educational Resources)?</strong></a><em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; </em></p>
<p><strong>Activity</strong>. As the definitions linked to above suggests, an OER could be a text or <a href="http://tlp.excellencegateway.org.uk/pdf/A2_Poster_AW_Layout_1.pdf" target="_self">PDF</a> file, a <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/smithsonian/3378997258/" target="_self">photograph</a>, <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/laurenpressley/educational-psychology" target="_self">a slideshow</a>, a video or audio file, a <a href="http://www2.le.ac.uk/departments/beyond-distance-research-alliance/projects/otter/the-oers/archaeology-and-ancient-history/sami-tent-in-second-life" target="_self">second life artifact</a> or an online assessment activity. Using the links below as a starting point:</p>
<ol>
<li> Find an OER which you may be able to use in your design.&nbsp;</li>
<li>Create a link to it here ('<em>add link'</em>)</li>
<li>Introduce yourself, your role and design and describe the OER you have chosen.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Useful links:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/2318" target="_self">Cloud: Resource: Links to OER repositories</a></li>
<li><a href="http://oerwiki.iiep-unesco.org/index.php?title=Main_Page" target="_self">UNESCO Community Wiki</a></li>
<li><a href="http://wikieducator.org/OER_Handbook/educator" target="_self">OER Educator handbook</a></li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>]]></description>
          <pubDate>Fri, 06 Nov 2009 12:22:00 +0000</pubDate>
