                    <item>
              <title>Activity: Clustering  research questions activity</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/1164</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/1164</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>An activity used in the <a href="/node/876">evidence and outcomes session </a>at the OER meeting in Monterey March 2009:</p>
<ul>
<li>Each person writes down one research question they are interested in on a post-it </li>
<li>Everyone goes around the room and reads other peoples&rsquo; questions</li>
<li>Those with a similar research question or focus cluster together</li>
<li>Clustered post-its are grouped on a board and a plenary session discusses and refines them.</li>
<li>A final activity can be to brainstorm evidence and examples of existing research or projects that are addressing or provide some answers to these research question </li>
</ul>]]></description>
          <pubDate>Mon, 16 Nov 2009 10:59:35 +0000</pubDate>
            </item>
